recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpSubratePhSize.description: Parameter Type = Immediate. Changes will not affect channels that are already connected. Size of the phasor (in bytes) on the subrate side of any ASM voice port using this trunk group.

recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpLocalSigConf.name: recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpLocalSigConf
recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpLocalSigConf.description: Parameter Type = Immediate. Changes will not affect channels that are already connected. AD-10 and ASM signalling incompatibility parameters.

recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpRemoteSigConf.name: recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpRemoteSigConf
recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpRemoteSigConf.description: Parameter Type = Immediate. Changes will not affect channels that are already connected. AD-10 and ASM signalling incompatibility parameters.

recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpRmtSigPattern.name: recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpRmtSigPattern
recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpRmtSigPattern.description: Parameter Type = Immediate. Changes will not affect channels that are already connected. Defines the remote signaling pattern on any ASM voice ports that use this trunk group. This pattern is delivered to receive signal channel connections at times prior to the availability of a verified reliable signal channel source.

recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpCelpNetSigMd.name: recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpCelpNetSigMd
recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpCelpNetSigMd.description: Parameter Type = Immediate. INTRODUCED 2.0.0 Enable autodetection of CELP/ATC channel connected equipment so as to automatically change format to become compatible with either LINK (5 byte) or ST (8 byte) channel modes. Alternately, this parameter hard sets CELP/ATC channels to be compatible only with either LINK or ST mode compatible equipment.

recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpSearchDir.name: recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpSearchDir
recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpSearchDir.description: Parameter Type = Immediate. INTRODUCED 2.0.0 Indicates the search order within the range specified by recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpLowElement and recfAsmVoiceTrkGrpHighElement attributes.

recfRtmPortStartMode.name: recfRtmPortStartMode
recfRtmPortStartMode.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Erase will reset all parameters to their default values.

recfRtmPortType.name: recfRtmPortType
recfRtmPortType.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Setting AD-3 or AD-7 will allocate all of the access device ports with their default parameters.

recfRtmPortPartitionID.name: recfRtmPortPartitionID
recfRtmPortPartitionID.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Default value is the partition ID of the node.

recfRtmAdPortStartMode.name: recfRtmAdPortStartMode
recfRtmAdPortStartMode.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Erase will reset all parameters to their default values.

recfRtmAdPortSpeed.name: recfRtmAdPortSpeed
recfRtmAdPortSpeed.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. If the speed is set to s56000 and recfRtmAdPortDataBits attribute set to b7, the channel will be transported as a 64000 bit stuffed channel. If the speed is set to s56000 and recfRtmAdPortDataBits attribute set to b8, the channel will be a subrate channel.

recfRtmAdPortDataBits.name: recfRtmAdPortDataBits
recfRtmAdPortDataBits.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Value b7 cannot be used in subrate connections.

recfLgmPortAddr.name: recfLgmPortAddr
recfLgmPortAddr.description: Parameter Type = Internal. This is a virtual port address in type:group:port format.

recfLgmPortStartMode.name: recfLgmPortStartMode
recfLgmPortStartMode.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Setting to erase will fail if the LGM port has any non-removed channels. If successful, returns the initial port configuration (with its default values) and erases any channels defined on this port.

recfLgmPortArq.name: recfLgmPortArq
recfLgmPortArq.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Specifies ARQ speed. Unit of bps, i which may not exceed the 9600.

recfLgmPortGroup.name: recfLgmPortGroup
recfLgmPortGroup.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Intended to force channels to use specific groups of LGM ports. There can be up to seven groups for each LGM port. Bit map bits 1 (lsb) to 7 indicates i the group(s) of the LGM.

recfLgmPortSatelliteHop.name: recfLgmPortSatelliteHop
recfLgmPortSatelliteHop.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Specifies the number of satellite hops per end - to - end point connection. Earth station - satellite - earth station connection represents one hop.

recfLgmPortSyncChar.name: recfLgmPortSyncChar
recfLgmPortSyncChar.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Specifies number of sync characters per frame.

recfLgmPortSyncLevel.name: recfLgmPortSyncLevel
recfLgmPortSyncLevel.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Synchronization level parameter.

recfLgmPortOosTimer.name: recfLgmPortOosTimer
recfLgmPortOosTimer.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. In units of seconds. The Out-Of-Service state is entered if this time is exceeded.

recfLgmPortPartitionID.name: recfLgmPortPartitionID
recfLgmPortPartitionID.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Used by security server to enforce shared node.

recfLgmPortBitMode.name: recfLgmPortBitMode
recfLgmPortBitMode.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Defines the bit mode of this port.

recfLgmPortInbandSuperrate.name: recfLgmPortInbandSuperrate
recfLgmPortInbandSuperrate.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Specifies how the signaling function transport for inband superrate is handled. <nack> - reject a channel connection with a NO BANDWIDTH response, so an alternative LINK path may be found. <forceActive> - sets all the functions active. <pass> - passes the functions the way they are set (slower than LINK).

recfLgmPortInbandSubrate.name: recfLgmPortInbandSubrate
recfLgmPortInbandSubrate.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Specifies how the signaling function transport for inband subrate is handled. <nack> - reject a channel connection with a NO BANDWIDTH response, so an alternative LINK path may be found. <pass> - passes the functions the way they are set (slower than LINK).

recfLgmPortOutbandSuperrate.name: recfLgmPortOutbandSuperrate
recfLgmPortOutbandSuperrate.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Specifies how the signaling function transport for outband superrate is handled. <nack> - reject a channel connection with a NO BANDWIDTH response, so an alternative LINK path may be found. <forceActive> - sets all the functions active. <pass> - passes the functions the way they are set (slower than LINK).

recfLgmPortOutbandSubrate.name: recfLgmPortOutbandSubrate
recfLgmPortOutbandSubrate.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Specifies how the signaling function transport for outband subrate is handled. <nack> - reject a channel connection with a NO BANDWIDTH response, so an alternative LINK path may be found. <pass> - passes the functions the way they are set (slower than LINK).

recfDsmIDCPortTable.name: recfDsmIDCPortTable
recfDsmIDCPortTable.description: This section of the MIB is not changeable. It is included so that the user can verify the existance of PVC port. The user can configure frame relay channels on these ports by using the recfFrChannelEntry section of the MIB.

recfDsmIDCPortAddr.name: recfDsmIDCPortAddr
recfDsmIDCPortAddr.description: Parameter Type = Internal. Port address format is nest.slot.65.

recfDsmDChPortTable.name: recfDsmDChPortTable
recfDsmDChPortTable.description: This MIB section is used to configure D-channel virtual ports. The user can configure TDM channels on these ports in the recfTDMChannelEntry section of the MIB. These TDM channels can connect at a rate of 64 kbps to a T1M or E1M common-channel signaling bundle.

recfDsmDChPortAddr.name: recfDsmDChPortAddr
recfDsmDChPortAddr.description: Parameter Type = Internal. Port address format is type.group.port. The server type is 131.

recfDsmDChPortStartMode.name: recfDsmDChPortStartMode
recfDsmDChPortStartMode.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. If set to off, then the D-channel cannot be connected. In order to set to erase, the D-channel must be disconnected.

recfDsmDChPortUpdate.name: recfDsmDChPortUpdate
recfDsmDChPortUpdate.description: Parameter Type = Internal. If set to resetReq, then the user must reset the port (which involves disconnecting and reconnecting the D-channel) in order for the parameter changes to take effect. If set to updateReq, then the user can update the port without affecting the D-channel connection in order for the parameter changes to take effect.

recfDsmDChPortPartitionID.name: recfDsmDChPortPartitionID
recfDsmDChPortPartitionID.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Used for security on shared nodes. The default value is the partition ID of the node.

recfDsmDChPortPbxProtocol.name: recfDsmDChPortPbxProtocol
recfDsmDChPortPbxProtocol.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Protocol used by the PBX using this D-channel. If the protocol type does not match the PBX protocol, then the port will not be able to come up.

recfDsmDChPortPbxLayer3Type.name: recfDsmDChPortPbxLayer3Type
recfDsmDChPortPbxLayer3Type.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. This parameter indicates whether the PBX or the DSM will be responsible for serving B-channels requests (layer 3 master or slave mode). If set to master DSM controls the assignment of B-channels. Otherwise the PBX controls it. To function properly, the DSM and PBX should be configured as different types.

recfDsmDChPortPbxLayer2Type.name: recfDsmDChPortPbxLayer2Type
recfDsmDChPortPbxLayer2Type.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. This parameter is independent of layer 3 master or slave mode. To function properly, the DSM and PBX should be configured as different types.

recfDsmDChPortSharedZeroFlag.name: recfDsmDChPortSharedZeroFlag
recfDsmDChPortSharedZeroFlag.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Indicates whether the zero bit of a frame's end flag can be combined with the zero bit of the next frame's start flag.

recfDsmDChPortActiveLev1CDRMode.name: recfDsmDChPortActiveLev1CDRMode
recfDsmDChPortActiveLev1CDRMode.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Specifies whether level 1 Call Detail Records for the calls in progress are to be collected for this D-channel. Changing this parameter will not disrupt any port operations.

recfDsmDChPortRecordLev1CDRMode.name: recfDsmDChPortRecordLev1CDRMode
recfDsmDChPortRecordLev1CDRMode.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Specifies whether level 1 Call Detail Records for the completed calls are to be collected for this D-channel. Changing this parameter will not disrupt any port operations.

recfDsmDChPortActiveLev2CDRMode.name: recfDsmDChPortActiveLev2CDRMode
recfDsmDChPortActiveLev2CDRMode.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Specifies whether level 2 Call Detail Records for the calls in progress are to be collected for this D-channel. Changing this parameter will not disrupt any port operations.

recfDsmDChPortRecordLev2CDRMode.name: recfDsmDChPortRecordLev2CDRMode
recfDsmDChPortRecordLev2CDRMode.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Specifies whether level 2 Call Detail Records for the completed calls are to be collected for this D-channel. Changing this parameter will not disrupt any port operations.

recfDsmDChPortCallsPerSecond.name: recfDsmDChPortCallsPerSecond
recfDsmDChPortCallsPerSecond.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. This attribute is an estimate of the number of calls per second (in units of 0.01 calls per second) on this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChBChTable.name: recfDsmDChBChTable
recfDsmDChBChTable.description: This MIB section is used to configure information about B-channels that are associated with the D-channel.

recfDsmDChBChAddr.name: recfDsmDChBChAddr
recfDsmDChBChAddr.description: Parameter Type = Internal. Port address of associated D-channel port. The format is type.group.port. The server type is 131.

recfDsmDChBChBundle.name: recfDsmDChBChBundle
recfDsmDChBChBundle.description: Parameter Type = Internal. Identifies the bundle which is associated with this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChBChDirection.name: recfDsmDChBChDirection
recfDsmDChBChDirection.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Specifies the direction of the calls on this B-channel. The values are: - outgoing: allows calls originating on PBX to ST - incoming: allows calls originating on ST to PBX - bidirectional: allows calls in any direction - none: this B-channel is not allowed for use. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port update will be required in order for the change to take effect. It will not disrupt any channel connections associated with this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChExchTable.name: recfDsmDChExchTable
recfDsmDChExchTable.description: This MIB section is used to assign up to 16 exchange codes to a D-channel.

recfDsmDChExchDChAddr.name: recfDsmDChExchDChAddr
recfDsmDChExchDChAddr.description: Parameter Type = Internal. D-channel port address. The format is type.group.port. The server type is 131.

recfDsmDChExchIndex.name: recfDsmDChExchIndex
recfDsmDChExchIndex.description: Parameter Type = Internal. Indexing the exchange code within this D-channel.

recfDsmDChExchControlMode.name: recfDsmDChExchControlMode
recfDsmDChExchControlMode.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Indicates whether this exchange code may be used to make a call. The value erase is used to wipe out the existing exchange code. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port update will be required in order for the change to take effect. It will not disrupt any channel connections associated with this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChExchCode.name: recfDsmDChExchCode
recfDsmDChExchCode.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. The valid characters are 0 - 9. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port update will be required in order for the change to take effect. It will not disrupt any channel connections associated with this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChQOSTable.name: recfDsmDChQOSTable
recfDsmDChQOSTable.description: This MIB section specifies the source node quality of service resolution entry that is to be used for the channel connection.

recfDsmDChQOSDChAddr.name: recfDsmDChQOSDChAddr
recfDsmDChQOSDChAddr.description: Parameter Type = Internal. Address of D-channel, for which this entry is being used.

recfDsmDChQOSIndex.name: recfDsmDChQOSIndex
recfDsmDChQOSIndex.description: Parameter Type = Internal. Index of the quality of service entry.

recfDsmDChQOSControlMode.name: recfDsmDChQOSControlMode
recfDsmDChQOSControlMode.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. Changes will not affect channels that are already connected. Disable will prevent this quality of service entry from being applied to the new voice connections. Erase will remove this quality of service entry from the table. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port update will be required in order for the change to take effect. It will not disrupt any channel connections associated with this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChQOSLowBChan.name: recfDsmDChQOSLowBChan
recfDsmDChQOSLowBChan.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. The low end of the source bundle range available for use by this D-channel. If this attribute is set to 0, then the used value is set to lowest valid number. The range is invalid if this attribute is set to the value greater than recfDsmDChQOSHighBChan. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port update will be required in order for the change to take effect. It will not disrupt any channel connections associated with this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChQOSHighBChan.name: recfDsmDChQOSHighBChan
recfDsmDChQOSHighBChan.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. The high end of the source bundle range available for use by this D-channel. If this attribute is set to 0, then the used value is set to highest valid number. The range is invalid if this attribute is not 0 and set to the value less than recfDsmDChQOSLowBChan. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port update will be required in order for the change to take effect. It will not disrupt any channel connections associated with this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChQOSLowExchCode.name: recfDsmDChQOSLowExchCode
recfDsmDChQOSLowExchCode.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. The valid characters are 0 - 9. The low end of the destination exchange codes range. The comparison type used is based upon the ASCII codes for the character string. Thus, for example, '5545' is less than '555'. If this attribute is set to an empty string, then the lowest valid value is used. The range is invalid if the value of this attribute is greater than recfDsmDChQOSHighExchCode. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port update will be required in order for the change to take effect. It will not disrupt any channel connections associated with this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChQOSHighExchCode.name: recfDsmDChQOSHighExchCode
recfDsmDChQOSHighExchCode.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. The valid characters are 0 - 9. The high end of the destination exchange codes range. The comparison type used is based upon the ASCII codes for the character string. Thus, for example, '5545' is less than '555'. If this attribute is set to an empty string, then the highest valid value is used. The range is invalid if the value of this attribute is not an empty string and less than recfDsmDChQOSLowExchCode. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port update will be required in order for the change to take effect. It will not disrupt any channel connections associated with this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChQOSCallType.name: recfDsmDChQOSCallType
recfDsmDChQOSCallType.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. This attribute specifies the call type. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port update will be required in order for the change to take effect. It will not disrupt any channel connections associated with this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChQOSChPrfIndex.name: recfDsmDChQOSChPrfIndex
recfDsmDChQOSChPrfIndex.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. This attribute specifies the channel profile table index that is defined in the channel profile MIB section on the source node. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port update will be required in order for the change to take effect. It will not disrupt any channel connections associated with this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChQOSSpecialPrfIndex.name: recfDsmDChQOSSpecialPrfIndex
recfDsmDChQOSSpecialPrfIndex.description: Parameter Type = Non-intrusive. This attribute specifies the special profile table index that is defined in the applicable profile MIB section on the source node (for example if the attribute recfDsmDChQOSCallType is set to voice, then the special profile table will be the scVoicePrf table). Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port update will be required in order for the change to take effect. It will not disrupt any channel connections associated with this D-channel port.

recfDsmDChDPNSSTable.name: recfDsmDChDPNSSTable
recfDsmDChDPNSSTable.description: This MIB section is used to configure D-channel DPNSS protocol related attributes.

recfDsmDChDPNSSAddr.name: recfDsmDChDPNSSAddr
recfDsmDChDPNSSAddr.description: Parameter Type = Internal. D-channel port address. Format is type.group.port. The server type is 131.

recfDsmDChDPNSSNL.name: recfDsmDChDPNSSNL
recfDsmDChDPNSSNL.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. The minimum number of retransmissions of a command frame if no acknowledge received. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChDPNSSNT1.name: recfDsmDChDPNSSNT1
recfDsmDChDPNSSNT1.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Duration for which retransmission is done (in units of 10 milliseconds). Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChDPNSSNT2.name: recfDsmDChDPNSSNT2
recfDsmDChDPNSSNT2.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Post retransmission acknowledge delay. In other words, this is an additional time after recfDsmDChDPNSSNL and recfDsmDChDPNSSNT1 expiration, before layer 2 informs layer 3 of a failure (in units of 10 milliseconds). If the PBX and DSM connected through a satellite, this attribute should be set to 52. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChDPNSSUnrecMsgIdle.name: recfDsmDChDPNSSUnrecMsgIdle
recfDsmDChDPNSSUnrecMsgIdle.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. If DSM has received unrecognized local PBX message, this setting specifies the idle time whithin which there will not be any outgoing calls attempted (in units of 1 second). Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChDPNSSInterDgtTmr.name: recfDsmDChDPNSSInterDgtTmr
recfDsmDChDPNSSInterDgtTmr.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Specifies the maximum time between PBX service request messages used to set up a call (in units of 1 second). If this time is exceeded call is cleared. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigTable.name: recfDsmDChQSigTable
recfDsmDChQSigTable.description: This MIB section is used to configure D-channel QSig protocol related attributes.

recfDsmDChQSigAddr.name: recfDsmDChQSigAddr
recfDsmDChQSigAddr.description: Parameter Type = Internal. D-channel port address. Format is type.group.port. The server type is 131.

recfDsmDChQSigK.name: recfDsmDChQSigK
recfDsmDChQSigK.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Maximum number of outstanding (unacknowledged) I-frames. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigN200.name: recfDsmDChQSigN200
recfDsmDChQSigN200.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Maximum number of frame retransmissions. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigT200.name: recfDsmDChQSigT200
recfDsmDChQSigT200.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Maximum time (in units of 1 second) before frame retransmission is initiated. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigT203.name: recfDsmDChQSigT203
recfDsmDChQSigT203.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Maximum time (in units of 1 second) allowed on layer 2 without frame exchange. If no frame is sent during this time, then layer 2 monitoring frame is sent. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigT302.name: recfDsmDChQSigT302
recfDsmDChQSigT302.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Maximum time between PBX service request messages used to set up a call (in units of 1 second). If this time is exceeded then the call is cleared. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigT303.name: recfDsmDChQSigT303
recfDsmDChQSigT303.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. SETUP message maximum response time (in units of 1 second). If exceeded, the SETUP messge will be sent once more. If there is still no response during this period of time, then the call is cleared. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigT304.name: recfDsmDChQSigT304
recfDsmDChQSigT304.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Maximum time (in units of 1 second) after receipt of SETUP ACK before one of the following messages is received: CALL PROCEEDING, ALERTING, CONNECT or DISCONNECT If while waiting DSM sends any message to PBX, the timer should be restarted. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigT305.name: recfDsmDChQSigT305
recfDsmDChQSigT305.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Maximum time (in units of 1 second) for DISCONNECT message response. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigT308.name: recfDsmDChQSigT308
recfDsmDChQSigT308.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Maximum time (in units of 1 second) for RELEASE message response. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigT309.name: recfDsmDChQSigT309
recfDsmDChQSigT309.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Maximum time (in units of 1 second) allowed to restore connection upon detection of a failure. If expired, both the connection and call are cleared. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigT314.name: recfDsmDChQSigT314
recfDsmDChQSigT314.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Maximum time (in units of 1 second) allowed to receive all of the segments of a message. This parameter applies only to segmented messages. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigT316.name: recfDsmDChQSigT316
recfDsmDChQSigT316.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Maximum time (in units of 1 second) for RESTART message response. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfDsmDChQSigT322.name: recfDsmDChQSigT322
recfDsmDChQSigT322.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Maximum time (in units of 1 second) for STATUS INQUIRY message. Changes to this field will be reflected in recfDsmDChPortUpdate. A port reset will be required in order for the change to take effect.

recfLink2TraIndex.name: recfLink2TraIndex
recfLink2TraIndex.description: Parameter Type = Internal. Translation table index, notated in Link-2 specific notation. Does not indicate any particular addresses, however must be set to the same value on both, Link-2 and ST-50 nodes. It is a link logical entity pointing to the translation table entry containing both, Link-2 and ST-50 physical addresses.

recfLink2TraStartMode.name: recfLink2TraStartMode
recfLink2TraStartMode.description: Parameter Type = Immediate. Setting to off will prevent this table entry from being used on connection (invalidates it). Setting to erase will free the entry.

recfLink2TraStAddr.name: recfLink2TraStAddr
recfLink2TraStAddr.description: Parameter Type = Immediate. Represents local ST-50 TDM channel Link2 channel (defined by recfLink2TraL2Addr attribute) is connected to. Used by ST-50 as a connection end point address.

recfLink2TraL2Addr.name: recfLink2TraL2Addr
recfLink2TraL2Addr.description: Parameter Type = Immediate. Represents Link2 address in Link2 network ST-50 TDM channel (defined by recfLink2TraStAddr attribute) is connected to. If this attribute has [:xch] part not equal zero, then it represents X50 subrate address, otherwise it is a regular address.

recfLink2TraFunctions.name: recfLink2TraFunctions
recfLink2TraFunctions.description: Parameter Type = Immediate. Selects the mode of functions exchange. In inBand mode the same time slot as data is being used. In outBand it is a separate channel.

recfLink2TraPartition.name: recfLink2TraPartition
recfLink2TraPartition.description: Parameter Type = Internal. Displays the partition assigned to this translation table entry. This partition is inherited from the TDM channel associated with this entry.

recfHwRscEngineTable.name: recfHwRscEngineTable
recfHwRscEngineTable.description: This MIB section is used for configuration of on-board engines on a module in an ST node. The engine configuration will be set up with default values when the module is configured in the recfSlotTable MIB. It will be erased when the module is erased from the recfSlotTable MIB.

recfHwRscEngineModuleAddr.name: recfHwRscEngineModuleAddr
recfHwRscEngineModuleAddr.description: The address of the module that this engine is located on. Format is <nest>.<slot>.

recfHwRscEngineID.name: recfHwRscEngineID
recfHwRscEngineID.description: The engine ID on the module.

recfHwRscEngineStartMode.name: recfHwRscEngineStartMode
recfHwRscEngineStartMode.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Controls whether the engine should start as inserted or removed when the module comes up. If the value is set to automatic, then the engine will start as inserted. Otherwise, it will start as removed.

recfHwRscEngineUpdate.name: recfHwRscEngineUpdate
recfHwRscEngineUpdate.description: Indicates if the current settings in the engine configuration MIB represent the active settings on the module or not. If this value is resetRequired, then an engine reset command is required for the current configuration to take effect. This is done by setting the MIB attribute restHwRscEngineDiagnostics to reset.

recfHwRscEngineApplication.name: recfHwRscEngineApplication
recfHwRscEngineApplication.description: Parameter Type = Intrusive. Used to reserve an engine for a specific application type. If no application type reservation is desired, then the value any should be used. If the application type specified is not supported for the module that the engine is located on, then the engine will not be able to be used for any applications. In this event, the module will generate an engine failure alarm to indicate a bad configuration.

restNodeDiagnostics.name: restNodeDiagnostics
restNodeDiagnostics.description: updateNest will update the node with the new nest number. If the new nest number is greater than the old number, then the new nests will be added, and any modules in those nests will be able to start running. If the new nest number is less than the old nest number, then the old nests and any modules in them will be removed. updateClockTable will update the clock fallback list. This will not affect the currently running clock, but will take affect when the current clock fails. The selectClock commands will force the specified clock to go active. It does not load the MIB configuration settings, but instead uses the current clock fallback list.

restNodeSWRevision.name: restNodeSWRevision
restNodeSWRevision.description: Version number of the NCP software that is currently running.

restNodeMIBRevision.name: restNodeMIBRevision
restNodeMIBRevision.description: Version number of the MIB schema that the NCP is currently using.

restNodeErrorMinutes.name: restNodeErrorMinutes
restNodeErrorMinutes.description: Count of the error minutes in the bus for the past 24 hours.

restNodeClockTableIndex.name: restNodeClockTableIndex
restNodeClockTableIndex.description: Indicates which clock in the clock fallback table is in use. If the clock status is slave holdover, then this field may return zero.

restNodeClockSubStatus.name: restNodeClockSubStatus
restNodeClockSubStatus.description: These are the substates associated with slaveHoldover state. If the clock status is not slaveHoldover, then notApplicable will be returned.

restNodeClockSourceType.name: restNodeClockSourceType
restNodeClockSourceType.description: Type of the clock currently in use. If the clock status is slave holdover, then this field may return not applicable.

restNodeClockSourcePort.name: restNodeClockSourcePort
restNodeClockSourcePort.description: Source port address of the clock currently in use, if the clock type is portRxInd, portRxDep, or portTx. If the clock type is a different value, then this field will be zero.

restNodeClockSourcePriority.name: restNodeClockSourcePriority
restNodeClockSourcePriority.description: Priority of the clock currently in use. If the clock status is slave holdover, then this field may return zero.

restNodeClockSourceQuality.name: restNodeClockSourceQuality
restNodeClockSourceQuality.description: Quality of the clock currently in use. If the clock status is slave holdover, then this field may return not applicable.

restNodeTestGenStatus.name: restNodeTestGenStatus
restNodeTestGenStatus.description: Current status of the test generator for TDM nDS0 channels.

restNodeTestGenType.name: restNodeTestGenType
restNodeTestGenType.description: Current type of the test generator for TDM nDS0 channels.

restNodeTestGenTDMChannel.name: restNodeTestGenTDMChannel
restNodeTestGenTDMChannel.description: Current channel address that the TDM test generator is being used on.

restNodeAlarmRelayStatus.name: restNodeAlarmRelayStatus
restNodeAlarmRelayStatus.description: Indicates whether the alarm relay port is programmed to be used or not.

restNodeAlarmRelaySubStatus.name: restNodeAlarmRelaySubStatus
restNodeAlarmRelaySubStatus.description: Indicates the status of the major alarm relay (first value) and the minor alarm relay (second value). This field is only valid if the alarm relay is enabled.

restNodeCpiStatus.name: restNodeCpiStatus
restNodeCpiStatus.description: Indicates the current status of the CPI port.

restNodeModemStatus.name: restNodeModemStatus
restNodeModemStatus.description: Indicates the current status of the modem port.

restNodeSoftloadStatus.name: restNodeSoftloadStatus
restNodeSoftloadStatus.description: Indicates the softload status. 'Idle' means that no softload has been run yet since the node went online. 'Softloading' indicates that a download is underway from an SNMS, CPS, or another node. 'Copy to standby NCP' means that a file is being transferred from the active NCP to the standby NCP. 'Copy to module' means that a file that is not stored on the NCP is being transferred to the module that is responsible for storing the file (for example, with AD-10 code, the file will be copied to the SGM/AG module that the AD-10 is connected to). 'Copy to online' means that a file is being transferred from the flash recovery area to its proper location in flash. 'Success' indicates that a download completed with no errors. The remaining values are used to indicate the different errors that can occur during a softload.

restNodeSoftloadTotal.name: restNodeSoftloadTotal
restNodeSoftloadTotal.description: Total number of bytes to be softloaded. If no softloading is in progress, then this value is zero.

restNodeSoftloadSize.name: restNodeSoftloadSize
restNodeSoftloadSize.description: Number of bytes that have been softloaded. Divide this by the value of restNodeSoftloadTotal to determine the completion percentage. If no softloading is in progress, then this value is zero.

restNodeSoftloadSoftwareType.name: restNodeSoftloadSoftwareType
restNodeSoftloadSoftwareType.description: Indicates type of software being transferred if a softload is in progress. notApplicable will be returned if no softload is in progress.

restNodeUploadStatus.name: restNodeUploadStatus
restNodeUploadStatus.description: Each upload client, which is used to upload files to SNMS or to other nodes, is represented by one octet. There are a maximum of eight upload clients per ST node. The possible values for a single octet (that is, a single upload client) are the following: idle(36) - no upload has occurred uploading(68) - upload is in progress success(65) - upload completed successfully noResource(106) - upload failure reason transmitFailure(107) - upload failure reason receiveFailure(108) - upload failure reason failure(43) - miscellaneous failure

restNodeUploadTotal.name: restNodeUploadTotal
restNodeUploadTotal.description: Total number of bytes to be uploaded to ech of up to eight clients. Each client uses four bytes for its value. If no uploading is in progress, then the value for that client will be zero.

restNodeUploadSize.name: restNodeUploadSize
restNodeUploadSize.description: Number of bytes that have been uploaded to each of up to eight clients. Each client uses four bytes for its value. Divide each client's value in this field by the corresponding value in restNodeUploadTotal to determine the completion percentage. If no uploading is in progress, then the value for that client will be zero.

restNodeUploadClientID.name: restNodeUploadClientID
restNodeUploadClientID.description: Specifies the node numbers of the eight clients that this node is serving during an upload. Each client is identified by two bytes. If the client is an EMS, then the value will be xFFFE.

restNodeTotalDsmCallsPerSecond.name: restNodeTotalDsmCallsPerSecond
restNodeTotalDsmCallsPerSecond.description: This is the total amount of calls per second (in units of 0.01 calls per second) allocated for DSM in this node.

restNestTable.name: restNestTable
restNestTable.description: This section of the MIB does not support getNext.

restNestDiagnostics.name: restNestDiagnostics
restNestDiagnostics.description: Remove will logically remove all of the modules in the nest, except the NCP, LXM, and RXM. This will free up the bus bandwidth. The configuration start mode of each module that is removed will be set to off. Insert will logically insert all of the modules in the nest, except the NCP, LXM, and RXM. The configuration MIB for each module will be loaded. The configuration start mode of each module that is inserted will be set to automatic. Reset will reset all modules in the nest except for the NCP, LXM, and RXM. It is equivalent to a remove followed by an insert, except that the configuration start modes in the slot MIBs are not changed. Reset right circuit will reset the RXM to circuit 1. Reset left circuit will reset the LXM to circuit 1. Toggle right circuit will toggle the circuit on the RXM. Toggle left circuit will toggle the circuit on the LXM. Set loopback LXM and set loopback RXM will loopback the appropriate end module in the nest. Clear loopback LXM and set loopback RXM will clear the loopback on the appropriate end module in the nest.

restNestSlotPresence.name: restNestSlotPresence
restNestSlotPresence.description: The lsb of the second octet represents slot 1, and the msb of the first octet represents slot 16. Slot 17 always has an RXM. Each bit set to 1 indicates that a module is present in that slot.

restSlotModuleDiagnostics.name: restSlotModuleDiagnostics
restSlotModuleDiagnostics.description: Remove will free bus bandwidth used by the ports of the module, and set the module start mode in the configuration MIB to off. Insert on a removed module will get the new MIB and software, and set the module start mode in the configuration MIB to automatic. Reset is equivalent to a remove and insert, except it does not change the module start mode in the configuration MIB. Update will load the non-intrusive parameters from the module configuration MIB. If any intrusive parameters have been changed, then update will fail.

restSlotModuleFailureType.name: restSlotModuleFailureType
restSlotModuleFailureType.description: If module status is fail, indicates what type of failure occurred. notApplicable will be returned if the module status is not fail. noRTS means that the module's run-time software is not on the NCP flash.

restSlotSWModuleSubType.name: restSlotSWModuleSubType
restSlotSWModuleSubType.description: All the subtypes are defined in recfSlotModuleSubType entry.

restSlotHWModuleSubType.name: restSlotHWModuleSubType
restSlotHWModuleSubType.description: All the subtypes are defined in recfSlotModuleSubType entry.

restSlotStartupDiagResults.name: restSlotStartupDiagResults
restSlotStartupDiagResults.description: Each bit displays the result (pass/fail) of a startup diagnostic. The bit map for the first four bytes is defined in recfSlotModuleStartDiagMask. The bit map for the last four bytes is defined in recfSlotModuleStartDiagMaskExt.

restSlotBGDiagResults.name: restSlotBGDiagResults
restSlotBGDiagResults.description: Each bit displays the result (pass/fail) of a background diagnostic. The bit map for the first four bytes is defined in recfSlotModuleBgdDiagMask. The bit map for the last four bytes is defined in recfSlotModuleBgdDiagMaskExt.

restSlotNumActivePorts.name: restSlotNumActivePorts
restSlotNumActivePorts.description: INTRODUCED 2.0.0 Number of ports on this module that have a restPortStatus value of active.

restSlotNumNormalPorts.name: restSlotNumNormalPorts
restSlotNumNormalPorts.description: INTRODUCED 2.0.0 Number of ports on this module that have a restPortCondition value of normal.

restNcpFlashObjectVersions.name: restNcpFlashObjectVersions
restNcpFlashObjectVersions.description: DEPRECATED 2.0.1 The information in this attribute has been replaced by the restNcpFlashTable section of the MIB. For each module type whose run-time software is stored in the NCP flash PROM, this attribute returns the software type (2 bytes), CRC (2 bytes), and version number (4 bytes). The values for software type match the enumerations for the attribute scSoftloadSoftwareType. If the flash PROM of the NCP cannot currently be read (such as when a softload is in progress), this attribute will return eight bytes with all zeros.

restNcpFlashTable.name: restNcpFlashTable
restNcpFlashTable.description: This MIB section lists all of the module object files stored in the flash PROM of the specified NCP. This section of the MIB does not support getNext. If the flash PROM is currently being written to, then all attributes in this MIB section will return an error.

restNcpFlashIndex.name: restNcpFlashIndex
restNcpFlashIndex.description: Used to differentiate the different module object files in the NCP flash PROM. This attribute does not contain any information about the file in flash.

restNcpFlashModuleType.name: restNcpFlashModuleType
restNcpFlashModuleType.description: The module type of this object file.

restNcpFlashRecoveryIndicator.name: restNcpFlashRecoveryIndicator
restNcpFlashRecoveryIndicator.description: Indicates whether or not this object file is stored in the softload recovery area.

restNcpFlashCompressIndicator.name: restNcpFlashCompressIndicator
restNcpFlashCompressIndicator.description: Indicates whether or not this object file is compressed or uncompressed.

restNcpFlashFileVersionNumber.name: restNcpFlashFileVersionNumber
restNcpFlashFileVersionNumber.description: The software revision number of this module object file.

restNcpFlashFileSize.name: restNcpFlashFileSize
restNcpFlashFileSize.description: The size of this module object file in bytes.

restNcpFlashFileStoredCrc.name: restNcpFlashFileStoredCrc
restNcpFlashFileStoredCrc.description: The stored CRC of this module object file.

restNcpFlashFileCrcCheck.name: restNcpFlashFileCrcCheck
restNcpFlashFileCrcCheck.description: If pass is returned, then the file image in flash passed a CRC check. If fail is returned, then the CRC check failed and the file is corrupted. If not applicable is returned, then we do not support CRC checking for this file on this NCP.

restFsmBypassBandwidth.name: restFsmBypassBandwidth
restFsmBypassBandwidth.description: Maximum available bypass capability in units of packets. Bypass capability is also limited by restFsmBandwidthAvail.

restFsmSourceBandwidth.name: restFsmSourceBandwidth
restFsmSourceBandwidth.description: Maximum available termination capability in units of packets. Termination capability also limited by restFsmBandwidthAvail.

restFsmBandwidthAvail.name: restFsmBandwidthAvail
restFsmBandwidthAvail.description: FSM available processing capability to serve new termination or bypass channel, in units of packets. This may be less than the sum of restFsmBypassBandwidth and restFsmSourceBandwidth.

restFsmPortSpeedAvail.name: restFsmPortSpeedAvail
restFsmPortSpeedAvail.description: FSM available port speed capability in units of bps. This only indicates the capability to support termination channels.

restFsmDlciTotal.name: restFsmDlciTotal
restFsmDlciTotal.description: Total number of DLCIs permitted on this FSM module.

restFsmDlciAvail.name: restFsmDlciAvail
restFsmDlciAvail.description: Number of DLCIs that can still be connected on this FSM module. The number of DLCIs that are connected on the module can be determined by subtracting this value from restFsmDlciTotal.

restFsmDlciConfig.name: restFsmDlciConfig
restFsmDlciConfig.description: Number of DLCIs that are configured on frame relay ports allocated to this FSM module. A new FSM port cannot be allocated on this module if the number of DLCIs configured on the port plus this value exceeds the value of restFsmDlciTotal. For FSM ports which are currently allocated, new DLCIs which are configured will increment this value. In this case, this value will be allowed to exceed restFsmDlciTotal so that existing channel connections will not be disrupted. However, the new DLCIs cannot be connected when restFsmDlciAvail is zero.

restFsmBypChanTotal.name: restFsmBypChanTotal
restFsmBypChanTotal.description: Total number of bypass channels permitted on this FSM module.

restFsmBypChanAvail.name: restFsmBypChanAvail
restFsmBypChanAvail.description: Number of bypass channels that can still be connected on this FSM module. The number of bypass channels that are connected on the module can be determined by subtracting this value from restFsmBypChanTotal.

restFsmVciCtrlBlkTotal.name: restFsmVciCtrlBlkTotal
restFsmVciCtrlBlkTotal.description: Total number of Vci Control Blocks allowed on FSM module. Each DLCI terminated on the module requires one Vci Control Block. Each bypass channel on the module requires two Vci Control Blocks.

restFsmVciCtrlBlkAvail.name: restFsmVciCtrlBlkAvail
restFsmVciCtrlBlkAvail.description: Number of available (unused) PVCs on FSM module. Each DLCI terminated on the module requires one Vci Control Block. Each bypass channel on the module requires two Vci Control Blocks.

restFsmTotalBuffers.name: restFsmTotalBuffers
restFsmTotalBuffers.description: Total number of channel buffers on FSM module.

restFsmBuffersAvail.name: restFsmBuffersAvail
restFsmBuffersAvail.description: Number of available (unused) channel buffers on FSM module.

restFsmCcfSupportIndicator.name: restFsmCcfSupportIndicator
restFsmCcfSupportIndicator.description: INTRODUCED 2.1.0 Indicates whether or not this module is capable of supporting CCFs.

restSgmAgmPortAvail.name: restSgmAgmPortAvail
restSgmAgmPortAvail.description: Number of AGM ports that are available for use on this SGM/AG module.

restSgmAgmPortTotal.name: restSgmAgmPortTotal
restSgmAgmPortTotal.description: Total number of AGM ports that are on this SGM/AG module.

restSgmAgSafAvail.name: restSgmAgSafAvail
restSgmAgSafAvail.description: Number of SAF ports that are available for use on this SGM/AG module.

restSgmAgSafTotal.name: restSgmAgSafTotal
restSgmAgSafTotal.description: Total number of SAF ports that are on this SGM/AG module.

restSgmAgSgmScfAvail.name: restSgmAgSgmScfAvail
restSgmAgSgmScfAvail.description: Number of SGM SCF ports that are available for use on this SGM/AG module. If the software type of the module is AGM, then zero shall be returned.

restSgmAgSgmScfTotal.name: restSgmAgSgmScfTotal
restSgmAgSgmScfTotal.description: Total number of SGM SCF ports that are on this SGM/AG module. If the software type of the module is AGM, then zero shall be returned.

restSgmAgAgmScfAvail.name: restSgmAgAgmScfAvail
restSgmAgAgmScfAvail.description: Number of AGM SCF ports that are available for use on this SGM/AG module. This value is valid for both SGM and AGM module software types.

restSgmAgAgmScfTotal.name: restSgmAgAgmScfTotal
restSgmAgAgmScfTotal.description: Total number of AGM SCF ports that are on this SGM/AG module. This value is valid for both SGM and AGM module software types.

restSgmAgAgmCcfAvail.name: restSgmAgAgmCcfAvail
restSgmAgAgmCcfAvail.description: INTRODUCED 2.1.0 Number of AGM CCF ports that are available for use on this SGM/AG module. This value is valid for both SGM and AGM module software types.

restSgmAgAgmCcfTotal.name: restSgmAgAgmCcfTotal
restSgmAgAgmCcfTotal.description: INTRODUCED 2.1.0 Total number of AGM CCF ports that are on this SGM/AG module. This value is valid for both SGM and AGM module software types.

restSgmAgAgmPortCapacity.name: restSgmAgAgmPortCapacity
restSgmAgAgmPortCapacity.description: INTRODUCED 2.1.0 List of AGM port speeds that are supported by this SGM/AG module. Every 4 bytes indicates one speed. The following speeds are supported: 19200 bps, 56000 bps, 64000 bps, 128000 bps

restAsmModuleMaxCelp.name: restAsmModuleMaxCelp
restAsmModuleMaxCelp.description: Indicates the number of CELP licenses on the module.

restAsmModuleNumCelpAvail.name: restAsmModuleNumCelpAvail
restAsmModuleNumCelpAvail.description: Indicates the number of CELP licenses on the module that are not in use.

restAsmModuleTotalEngines.name: restAsmModuleTotalEngines
restAsmModuleTotalEngines.description: Indicates the total number of DSP engines on the module.

restAsmModuleAvailEngines.name: restAsmModuleAvailEngines
restAsmModuleAvailEngines.description: Indicates the currently available (unused) number of DSP engines on the module.

restAsmModuleTotalSafScfs.name: restAsmModuleTotalSafScfs
restAsmModuleTotalSafScfs.description: Indicates the total number of SAFs and SCFs that can be allocated on this ASM module.

restAsmModuleAvailSafScfs.name: restAsmModuleAvailSafScfs
restAsmModuleAvailSafScfs.description: Indicates the currently available (unused) number of SAFs and SCFs on this ASM module.

restAsmEngineTable.name: restAsmEngineTable
restAsmEngineTable.description: This section of the MIB doesn't support getNext

restAsmEngineModuleAddr.name: restAsmEngineModuleAddr
restAsmEngineModuleAddr.description: Physical address of the ASM module

restAsmEngineID.name: restAsmEngineID
restAsmEngineID.description: The engine ID on ASM module

restAsmEngineStatus.name: restAsmEngineStatus
restAsmEngineStatus.description: These applications cannot be on the same engine at the same time

restAsmEngineNumSAFs.description: Number of SAF ports. If none returns zero

restAsmEngineNumSCFs.name: restAsmEngineNumSCFs
restAsmEngineNumSCFs.description: Number of SCF ports. If none returns zero

restAsmEngineApplication.name: restAsmEngineApplication
restAsmEngineApplication.description: Indicates the type of application allocated on this DSP engine, if any.

restAsmModApplTable.name: restAsmModApplTable
restAsmModApplTable.description: This section of the MIB enables the user to determine the availability of specific resource types on an ASM module based upon the current resource allocation. This section of the MIB doesn't support getNext

restAsmModApplModuleAddr.name: restAsmModApplModuleAddr
restAsmModApplModuleAddr.description: Physical address of the ASM module

restAsmModApplMaxPortsAllowed.name: restAsmModApplMaxPortsAllowed
restAsmModApplMaxPortsAllowed.description: The maximum number of ports which can be allocated on the ASM module running the specified application. This value assumes that the module is running no other applications. This value is based on the following factors: (1) total number of DSP engines on the module (2) total number of ports allowed on the module (3) total number of application licenses on the module, if the application is licensed (4) module application type.

restAsmModApplCurPortsAllowed.name: restAsmModApplCurPortsAllowed
restAsmModApplCurPortsAllowed.description: The current number of ports which can be allocated on the ASM module running the specified application. This determines how many ports can still be allocated based on what resources are currently allocated on the module. It indicates how many more ports of this application can be added if all new allocations are ports running this application. The total number of ports that can still be allocated in a mixed application scenario is NOT the sum of all of these values for each application. The value of this value is based on the following factors: (1) number of unallocated DSP engines (2) available ports on DSP engines which are already allocated for this application type (3) number of ports that can still be allocated on the module (4) licenses available, if the application is licensed (5) module application type.

restAsmModApplCurPortsAllocated.name: restAsmModApplCurPortsAllocated
restAsmModApplCurPortsAllocated.description: The current number of ports which are allocated on the ASM module and are running the specified application.

restAsmModApplEnginesUsed.name: restAsmModApplEnginesUsed
restAsmModApplEnginesUsed.description: The total number of DSP engines on the ASM module that are currently allocated for this application type.

restAsmModApplEnginesRsvd.name: restAsmModApplEnginesRsvd
restAsmModApplEnginesRsvd.description: The total number of unallocated DSP engines on the ASM module that are reserved for this application type.

restAsmModApplTotalLicenses.name: restAsmModApplTotalLicenses
restAsmModApplTotalLicenses.description: The total number of licenses available on the ASM module for this application type. If the application is unlicensed, then a value of zero shall be returned.

restAsmModApplAvailLicenses.name: restAsmModApplAvailLicenses
restAsmModApplAvailLicenses.description: A count of the licenses on the ASM module for this application type which are not currently in use. If the application is unlicensed, then a value of zero shall be returned.

restRtmModuleDS0sUsed.name: restRtmModuleDS0sUsed
restRtmModuleDS0sUsed.description: Current number of DS0 connections from AD-x units on this module.

restRtmModuleDS0sAvail.name: restRtmModuleDS0sAvail
restRtmModuleDS0sAvail.description: With the current number of DS0 and SAF connections, this field specifies the number of DS0 connections that could still be made assuming no more SAF connections are made.

restRtmModuleSafsUsed.name: restRtmModuleSafsUsed
restRtmModuleSafsUsed.description: Current number of SAF connections from AD-x units on this module.

restRtmModuleSafsAvail.name: restRtmModuleSafsAvail
restRtmModuleSafsAvail.description: With the current number of DS0 and SAF connections, this field specifies the number of SAF connections that could still be made assuming no more DS0 connections are made.

restDsmModuleTable.name: restDsmModuleTable
restDsmModuleTable.description: This section of the MIB is used to get status of any DSM modules defined on the node.

restDsmModuleAddr.name: restDsmModuleAddr
restDsmModuleAddr.description: Address of this DSM module. Format is nest.slot.

restDsmModuleNumDsmComms.name: restDsmModuleNumDsmComms
restDsmModuleNumDsmComms.description: Number of DSMs that this DSM is able to communicate with.

restDsmModuleNumCallsProc.name: restDsmModuleNumCallsProc
restDsmModuleNumCallsProc.description: Number of calls in the non-idle state (in the process of connection, connected or in the process of disconnection).

restDsmModuleNumRmtRteEntries.name: restDsmModuleNumRmtRteEntries
restDsmModuleNumRmtRteEntries.description: Total number of entries allowed in the remote routing table.

restDsmModuleNumRmtRteAvail.name: restDsmModuleNumRmtRteAvail
restDsmModuleNumRmtRteAvail.description: Number of entries in the remote routing table that are available. The number of occupied entries can be determined by subtracting this value from restDsmModuleNumRmtRteEntries.

restDsmModuleNumLocRteEntries.name: restDsmModuleNumLocRteEntries
restDsmModuleNumLocRteEntries.description: Total number of entries allowed in the local routing table.

restDsmModuleNumLocRteAvail.name: restDsmModuleNumLocRteAvail
restDsmModuleNumLocRteAvail.description: Number of entries in the local routing table that are available. The number of occupied entries can be determined by subtracting this value from restDsmModuleNumLocRteEntries.

restDsmModuleBypassPPSTotal.name: restDsmModuleBypassPPSTotal
restDsmModuleBypassPPSTotal.description: Total bypass throughput allowed on this DSM module in units of packets per second.

restDsmModuleBypassPPSAvail.name: restDsmModuleBypassPPSAvail
restDsmModuleBypassPPSAvail.description: Available bypass capability in units of packets per second. The currently being used bypass throughput on the module can be determined by subtracting this value from restDsmModuleBypassPPSTotal.

restDsmModuleBypChanTotal.name: restDsmModuleBypChanTotal
restDsmModuleBypChanTotal.description: Total number of bypass channels permitted on this DSM module.

restDsmModuleBypChanAvail.name: restDsmModuleBypChanAvail
restDsmModuleBypChanAvail.description: Number of bypass channels that can still be connected on this DSM module. The number of bypass channels that are connected on the module can be determined by subtracting this value from restDsmModuleBypChanTotal.

restDsmModuleCirTotal.name: restDsmModuleCirTotal
restDsmModuleCirTotal.description: Total CIR on this DSM module.

restDsmModuleCirAvail.name: restDsmModuleCirAvail
restDsmModuleCirAvail.description: Available (unused) CIR on this DSM module. The currently being used CIR can be determined by subtracting this value from restDsmModuleBypChanTotal.

restDsmModuleVciCtrlBlkTotal.name: restDsmModuleVciCtrlBlkTotal
restDsmModuleVciCtrlBlkTotal.description: Total number of Vci Control Blocks allowed on this DSM module. Each DLCI terminated on the module requires one Vci Control Block. Each bypass channel on the module requires two Vci Control Blocks.

restDsmModuleVciCtrlBlkAvail.name: restDsmModuleVciCtrlBlkAvail
restDsmModuleVciCtrlBlkAvail.description: Number of available (unused) PVCs on this DSM module. Each DLCI terminated on the module requires one Vci Control Block. Each bypass channel on the module requires two Vci Control Blocks.

restDsmModuleTotalBuffers.name: restDsmModuleTotalBuffers
restDsmModuleTotalBuffers.description: Total number of channel buffers allowed on this DSM module.

restDsmModuleBuffersAvail.name: restDsmModuleBuffersAvail
restDsmModuleBuffersAvail.description: Number of available (unused) channel buffers on DSM module. The number of channel buffers that are currently being used on the module can be determined by subtracting this value from restDsmModuleTotalBuffers.

restDsmModuleTotalRecCDRs.name: restDsmModuleTotalRecCDRs
restDsmModuleTotalRecCDRs.description: Total number of recorded CDRs allowed on this DSM module. This value is counted across all CDR logs

restDsmModuleRecCDRsAvail.name: restDsmModuleRecCDRsAvail
restDsmModuleRecCDRsAvail.description: Number of available (unused) CDRs on this DSM module. These CDRs may be assigned to any of the CDR logs defined on this DSM module.

restDsmModuleTotalCallsPerSec.name: restDsmModuleTotalCallsPerSec
restDsmModuleTotalCallsPerSec.description: This is the total amount of calls per second (in units of 0.01 calls per second) that can be handled by this DSM.

restDsmModuleCallsPerSecAvail.name: restDsmModuleCallsPerSecAvail
restDsmModuleCallsPerSecAvail.description: This is the amount of calls per second (in units of 0.01 calls per second) that can be allocated on this DSM. The number of calls per second currently allocated to the module can be determined by subtracting this number from the value of restDsmModuleTotalCallsPerSec attribute.

restDsmModuleCallsPerSecFactor.name: restDsmModuleCallsPerSecFactor
restDsmModuleCallsPerSecFactor.description: This is the conversion factor between calls per second (in units of 0.01 calls per second) and processing units. The equation is: processing units = this value * calls per second.

restDsmModuleBypassFactor.name: restDsmModuleBypassFactor
restDsmModuleBypassFactor.description: This is the conversion factor between bypass bandwidth (in PPS) and processing units. The equation is: processing units = this value * bypass bandwidth.

restDsmModuleTotalProcessUnits.name: restDsmModuleTotalProcessUnits
restDsmModuleTotalProcessUnits.description: This is a rating for the total number of D-channel calls per second and bypass bandwidth allowed on this DSM. The two quantities are converted to the same units using the values of the restDsmModuleCallsPerSecFactor and restDsmModuleBypassFactor attributes.

restDsmModuleProcessUnitsAvail.name: restDsmModuleProcessUnitsAvail
restDsmModuleProcessUnitsAvail.description: This is a rating of the number of the number of D-channel calls per second and bypass bandwidth that is unused on this DSM. To determine the amount that is currently allocated, subtract this value from restDsmModuleTotalProcessUnits attribute value.

restDsmModRecCDRLogIndex.name: restDsmModRecCDRLogIndex

restDsmModRecCDRLogStatus.name: restDsmModRecCDRLogStatus
restDsmModRecCDRLogStatus.description: This CDR log overflow flag status.

restDsmModRecCDRLogLev1Entries.name: restDsmModRecCDRLogLev1Entries
restDsmModRecCDRLogLev1Entries.description: Number of level 1 CDRs for this CDR log.

restDsmModRecCDRLogLev2Entries.name: restDsmModRecCDRLogLev2Entries
restDsmModRecCDRLogLev2Entries.description: Number of level 2 CDRs for this CDR log.

restDsmModRecCDRLogClrEntries.name: restDsmModRecCDRLogClrEntries
restDsmModRecCDRLogClrEntries.description: Number of entries on this CDR log to be cleared, counting from the oldest record.

restDsmModRecCDRTable.name: restDsmModRecCDRTable
restDsmModRecCDRTable.description: This section of the MIB contains the status of a Call Detail Records for completed call.

restDsmModRecCDRAddr.name: restDsmModRecCDRAddr
restDsmModRecCDRAddr.description: Address of this DSM module. Format is nest.slot.

restDsmModRecCDRLogNum.name: restDsmModRecCDRLogNum
restDsmModRecCDRLogNum.description: Specifies the CDR log number to be accessed on this DSM module.

restDsmModRecCDRIndex.name: restDsmModRecCDRIndex
restDsmModRecCDRIndex.description: Identifies the Call Detail Record to be accessed on this log based on its position (counting from the oldest one).

restDsmModRecCDRContents.name: restDsmModRecCDRContents
restDsmModRecCDRContents.description: Call Detail Record from a module CDR log. These CDRs are for completed calls. The bytes in a CDR for a completed call are interpretted as follows: 1: CDR type, values are: level 1 (1) level 2 (2) 2: version number 3-4: partition ID 5-6: call ID 7: protocol type, values are: DPNSS (1) Q.Sig (2) 8: unused From this position down the contents definition varies, depending on the interface level (CDR type). For Level 1 CDRs (Physical Characteristics): 9-12: originating time 13-16: answer time 17-20: disconnect time 21-22: B-channel source node ID 23: B-channel source nest ID 24: B-channel source slot ID 25-26: B-channel source port ID 27-28: B-channel source channel ID 29-30: B-channel destination node ID 31: B-channel destination nest ID 32: B-channel destination slot ID 33-34: B-channel destination port ID 35-36: B-channel destination channel ID 37: call type, values are: real (3) virtual (0) 38: special profile type, values defined in attribute recfDsmDChQOSCallType 39: info type, values are: Q.Sig speech (0) DPNSS A-law (1) DPNSS ADPCM (2) DPNSS Mu-law (3) Unrestricted data (8) Restricted data (9) 3.1 KHz audio (16) 7 KHz audio (17) video (24) 40: special profile index 41: channel profile index 42: NCP clear cause - values are defined in recfTDMChannelState 43: clear cause, values are: (If NCP clear cause is not zero, this byte is not used.) - DPNSS values: number unobtainable (0) address incomplete (1) network termination (2) service unavailable (3) subscriber incompatible (4) congestion/collision (7) busy (8) subscriber out of service (9) incoming calls barred (10) service incompatible (19) acknowledgement (20) signal not understood (21) signal not valid (22) service temporarily unavailable (23) facility not registered (24) reject (25) message not understood (26) signalling system incompatible (27) route out of service (28) transferred (29) network address extension error (30) no free channel or channel unavailable from NCP (34) channel out of service (35) priority forced release (36) access barred (41) requested channel unavailable(44) DTE controlled not ready (45) DTE uncontrolled not ready (46) normal call termination (48) unbinding (101) version invalid (103) B-channel failure cause (112) D-channel failure cause (113) socket failure cause (114) - Q.Sig values: (supported in Release 2.0.2) no cause (0) no route (3) channel unacceptable (6) normal call clearing (16) user busy (17) no user responding (18) no answer (19) call rejected (21) number changed (22) out of order (27) T302 timer expiration or invalid number format (28) status response (30) normal unspecified (31) no free channel or channel unavailable from NCP (34) link reset or temporary failure (41) requested channel unavailable(44) bearer not authorized (57) bearer not available (58) service not available (63) bearer not implemented (65) invalid call reference (81) incompatible destination (88) no bearer capability or no address or mandatory element missing (96) message type not implemented (97) message type incompatible (98) information type not implemented (99) invalid information element contents (100) unbinding (101) recovery on timer expiry (102) version invalid (103) protocol error (111) B-channel failure cause (112) D-channel failure cause (113) socket failure cause (114) 44: number of call attempts between DSMs 45-48: transmission rate For Level 2 CDRs (Data Link Layer): 9-12: setup final time 13-16: connect request time 17-20: connect response time 21-22: source node ID 23: source nest ID 24: source slot ID 25-26: destination node ID 27: destination nest ID 28: destination slot ID 29: calling number size (number of bytes, not string length) - this number is referred to from now on as x 30-(29+x): calling number (30+x): called number size (number of bytes, not string length) - this number is referred to from now on as y (31+x)-(30+x+y): called number (31+x+y): routing digits (32+x+y): unused.

restDsmModExchCallNumber.description: The call number. The valid character set is defined in recfDsmDChExchTable MIB section.

restDsmModExchPartition.name: restDsmModExchPartition
restDsmModExchPartition.description: The partition id of the instance the user is inquiring information on. Partition 1 (global) should not match the instance partition id. It is able to obtain an info for any partition.

restDsmModExchCode.name: restDsmModExchCode
restDsmModExchCode.description: The call numbers matched exchange code. If there is no matched exchange code, an error message will be returned. The valid character set is defined in recfDsmDChExchTable MIB section.

restDsmModRteExchCodeLen.name: restDsmModRteExchCodeLen
